FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell visited Surfside, FL, where a residential building partially collapsed. Criswell described the scene as indescribable and provided updates on meetings with state and local officials. The article expresses gratitude for the first responders, search and rescue teams, and various personnel working tirelessly to save lives and assist survivors. The administration is prepared to offer any necessary support. The families affected by the tragedy are enduring an unimaginably difficult time, with the uncertainty adding to their pain.